(55, 'Punch-Drunk Love', '2002-11-01', 95, 'A psychologically troubled novelty supplier is nudged towards a romance with an English woman, all the while being extorted by a phone-sex line run by a crooked mattress salesman, and purchasing stunning amounts of pudding.', 'Comedy', '7.3', 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYmE1OTY4NjgtYjcwNC00NWE4LWJiNGMtZmVhYTdlMWE1YzIxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTMxODk2OTU@._V1_SX300.jpg', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/KGqn5k227HY?si=x03DlNyE1SUQ5g3Y\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', 'https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZmI4M2FiOGItZDM3NC00YWQ3LTlkZWYtMjA4Mjc3Y2U0Yzk3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMDM2NDM2MQ@@._V1_.jpg', 'Justin Chadwick', 'Natalie Portman, Scarlett Johansson, Eric Bana'),
